1
00:00:31,904 --> 00:00:35,008
=Love Actually S5=

2
00:00:38,688 --> 00:00:41,759
(The House, Hainan)

3
00:00:41,759 --> 00:00:43,279
Bye-bye. See you in Shanghai. Bye-bye.

4
00:00:43,279 --> 00:00:44,439
See you in Shanghai.

5
00:00:53,376 --> 00:00:54,976
(The House, Shanghai)

6
00:00:56,959 --> 00:00:57,919
We're finally back.

7
00:00:58,799 --> 00:00:59,560
We're home.

8
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,040
We're home.

9
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:03,880
Welcome to the Shanghai house, Ji Yu.

10
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,519
Yes, welcome.

11
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:06,120
You're back.

12
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:07,519
Hello.

13
00:01:07,519 --> 00:01:08,000
Hello.

14
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:09,400
Mr. Dong.

15
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:11,000
Look at this.

16
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:12,919
What is it?

17
00:01:15,199 --> 00:01:15,639
What's wrong?

18
00:01:15,639 --> 00:01:16,279
Take a look.

19
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:18,639
This is mine.

20
00:01:18,639 --> 00:01:20,000
Chen Jianying has left.

21
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:20,760
Why?

22
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,639
She wrote a letter for everyone.

23
00:01:23,519 --> 00:01:24,360
Seeing the words
is like seeing me in person.

24
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:25,680
Your presence made me realize

25
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:27,776
that there truly is understanding
in this world.

26
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:31,120
This kind of care always touches

27
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,000
the softest part of my heart.

28
00:01:33,919 --> 00:01:35,440
We seem to be

29
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,120
two strange individuals

30
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,400
in this fast-paced life,

31
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:41,152
yet we are understood and accompanied

32
00:01:42,279 --> 00:01:43,919
because of our similarities.

33
00:01:43,919 --> 00:01:45,720
What a grateful encounter this is.

34
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,120
It was a bit sudden.

35
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:52,360
I planned to invite her
to an exhibition back in Shanghai.

36
00:01:53,199 --> 00:01:54,440
Go to Beijing to see it with her.

37
00:02:10,399 --> 00:02:12,199
I need a few people
to help me get the takeout.

38
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,144
There are seven or eight bags.

39
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,720
Let's go. I'll go with you.

40
00:02:17,344 --> 00:02:18,368
A few days ago,

41
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,000
Chen Jianying was like,

42
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,479
as long as we were together,

43
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:23,279
she would stay with us.

44
00:02:23,279 --> 00:02:25,440
And she said a couple of days ago

45
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:28,479
that she felt her journey here
had come to an end.

46
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,360
I always thought

47
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,919
she was joking.

48
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:32,160
No.

49
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,440
I think she probably felt

50
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:35,160
that after coming back here,

51
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,864
we'd just have fun.

52
00:02:36,864 --> 00:02:37,440
Yeah.

53
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,479
So when she said

54
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:40,880
her journey had come to an end,

55
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,759
she had made up her mind.

56
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:44,800
Come on.

57
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,199
All of it.

58
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:46,559
All of it?

59
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,199
Can she come back?

60
00:02:52,288 --> 00:02:53,216
Can she make a return?

61
00:02:53,216 --> 00:02:54,360
She can't just disappear like this.

62
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,000
Can we ask her

63
00:02:55,679 --> 00:02:56,759
to come back when the time comes?

64
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:57,119
Yeah.

65
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,960
Here's something to cheer you up.

66
00:03:19,584 --> 00:03:20,720
Come on, I'll give it to you later.

67
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,399
Let's go out first.

68
00:03:23,279 --> 00:03:23,880
Are you cold?

69
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,160
I'm okay.

70
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,440
I'll fetch it and come back.

71
00:03:27,199 --> 00:03:27,919
You're wearing shorts.

72
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:28,520
You should put on some pants.

73
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,720
Do you still have to pretend

74
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:30,679
as if you didn't know about this?

75
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,320
It must be tough for you.

76
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,800
But when I was reading
the journal just now,

77
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:37,080
I was crying so hard
I was a bit convulsed.

78
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:39,399
Are you feeling better now?

79
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:40,960
I felt better the moment I saw you.

80
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:43,199
Look at this.

81
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:44,119
Do you recognize where this is?

82
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,080
And this is...

83
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,600
For the seaside,

84
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,000
I found a hair clip

85
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,448
that matches your style.

86
00:03:52,448 --> 00:03:53,399
Wear it tomorrow.

87
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,320
Tomorrow.

88
00:04:06,656 --> 00:04:09,920
(A gift for Lu Bingkun)

89
00:04:16,799 --> 00:04:17,320
And this is you.

90
00:04:18,359 --> 00:04:19,279
Why am I a shark?

91
00:04:19,799 --> 00:04:20,440
Then tell me.

92
00:04:21,376 --> 00:04:22,519
Why are you a piggy?

93
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:25,720
Cute.

94
00:04:26,079 --> 00:04:27,040
Is this a keychain?

95
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:27,679
So I can attach them?

96
00:04:27,679 --> 00:04:28,640
Hang it here.

97
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,720
I'll hang it here for now.

98
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,880
Hang it here for now.

99
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,320
I should stand behind the door number.

100
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:34,920
Okay.

101
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:40,040
This is your fluffy jacket.

102
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,320
This jacket looks nice.

103
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,760
It goes well with my white jacket.

104
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:44,640
Which jacket?

105
00:04:45,079 --> 00:04:46,784
The one I wore that day,

106
00:04:46,784 --> 00:04:48,064
the fuzzy sweater.

107
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,280
You ordered takeout too?

108
00:04:49,559 --> 00:04:50,720
I didn't order takeout.

109
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:52,320
For everyone...

110
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,440
Bought some things...

111
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:53,760
Yeah.

112
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,688
(Gifts prepared for everyone)

113
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:55,920
This one I took out

114
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,519
is a bottle opener for Big Bro.

115
00:04:57,519 --> 00:04:57,959
Fridge.

116
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:58,640
Fridge magnet.

117
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:59,720
An opener.

118
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,040
That's so thoughtful.

119
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,839
And "No Anxiety".

120
00:05:06,119 --> 00:05:06,959
Is it a fridge magnet?

121
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:07,920
Yes, a fridge magnet.

122
00:05:08,839 --> 00:05:10,839
This is for Xuan.

123
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:12,079
Wishing you overnight riches.

124
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:12,519
Thank you.

125
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:15,040
Since Wentao is a musician.

126
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,040
He is pure.

127
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,799
So here's a pure coconut, Wentao.

128
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:18,920
Thank you.

129
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,119
You're welcome.

130
00:05:20,119 --> 00:05:21,959
And this is for Liu.

131
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:23,440
Because the feeling she gives me

132
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,600
is very bright.

133
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:27,279
And...

134
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,079
So beautiful.

135
00:05:28,079 --> 00:05:30,399
This is for Danqi.

136
00:05:30,399 --> 00:05:31,600
And

137
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,920
this is a mango.

138
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,399
This is a mango flower.

139
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:35,959
So I hope you guys can...

140
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,279
(Mischievous ideas brewing)

141
00:05:38,279 --> 00:05:39,720
Blossom and bear fruit.

142
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,720
Thank you.

143
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:44,760
And also...

144
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:47,279
Zhuoran?

145
00:05:47,959 --> 00:05:48,720
Actually,

146
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:50,079
this is for Zhuoran.

147
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:51,399
This is for Chen Jianying.

148
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:53,040
I'll put it here for now.

149
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,040
And this is for Lizheng.

150
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,359
Thank you.

151
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,399
What's the meaning behind this?

152
00:05:58,399 --> 00:05:59,839
No special meaning.

153
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:00,399
Okay.

154
00:06:02,359 --> 00:06:02,920
Seashells.

155
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,079
Let's eat first.

156
00:06:08,959 --> 00:06:09,480
Want one?

157
00:06:10,239 --> 00:06:11,079
Have another one of those.

158
00:06:12,959 --> 00:06:14,399
I'll call him.

159
00:06:14,399 --> 00:06:15,239
Call him.

160
00:06:15,239 --> 00:06:16,399
Call him.

161
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,279
Zhuoran needs some time alone
to process things.

162
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:23,279
Mr. Dong.

163
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,040
Yes?

164
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,640
Feeling better?

165
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,920
I'm here on orders to escort you

166
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,040
down for dinner.

167
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,119
I'm not eating; you guys go ahead.

168
00:06:33,119 --> 00:06:33,640
I'm not hungry anymore.

169
00:06:34,119 --> 00:06:34,359
No,

170
00:06:34,359 --> 00:06:35,640
come down.

171
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,519
Just hang out for a bit.

172
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:36,839
Let's go.

173
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,559
I want to be alone for a while.

174
00:06:38,559 --> 00:06:39,720
Tidy up a bit.

175
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,000
You guys go ahead.

176
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:42,880
Then you have your quiet time.

177
00:06:43,399 --> 00:06:44,079
You go first.

178
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:44,760
I'll tidy up.

179
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,160
I happen to have something to do.

180
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:46,720
It's fine.

181
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,079
It's nothing.

182
00:06:48,079 --> 00:06:49,000
I'll leave the door open for you then.

183
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,399
He's going to tidy up his room.

184
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:58,399
Let him tidy up his room.

185
00:06:58,799 --> 00:06:59,760
Is Mr. Dong okay?

186
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,440
What is he doing?

187
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,440
Tidying up his room.

188
00:07:09,984 --> 00:07:10,368
(Serving food x1)

189
00:07:10,752 --> 00:07:11,200
(Serving food x2)

190
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:14,200
I'm eating like it's a buffet,

191
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,880
getting one of each dish first.

192
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,959
(A full bowl)

193
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:18,720
A flowing feast.

194
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,920
Let me get you some noodles.

195
00:07:25,399 --> 00:07:26,959
I really feel like I'm at a buffet.

196
00:07:27,559 --> 00:07:28,640
A buffet is great.

197
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,279
Why did you sit there?

198
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:32,440
I asked you to move over one seat,
but you didn't.

199
00:07:33,359 --> 00:07:34,000
I didn't?

200
00:07:34,519 --> 00:07:35,239
Really?

201
00:07:35,239 --> 00:07:36,359
I asked you twice to move,
but you didn't.

202
00:07:37,559 --> 00:07:38,239
I didn't hear you.

203
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,000
(First time)
Move over.

204
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,239
Then you guys move
one more seat that way.

205
00:07:41,792 --> 00:07:43,104
(Misunderstanding)

206
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,239
(Second time)
You guys need to move one seat in.

207
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,799
(Didn't hear again)
Sit down.

208
00:07:47,799 --> 00:07:48,679
I'm dying of laughter.

209
00:07:48,679 --> 00:07:49,920
You sit here, and I'll sit over there.

210
00:07:50,079 --> 00:07:51,079
Then let's move one seat over, okay?

211
00:07:51,079 --> 00:07:51,839
Move one seat over.

212
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:53,359
He asked you to move one seat over.

213
00:07:53,359 --> 00:07:54,679
Leave the seat for him.

214
00:07:54,679 --> 00:07:55,519
It's fine.

215
00:07:55,519 --> 00:07:56,559
Just eat.

216
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:56,839
Come on.

217
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:58,559
What's the big deal?

218
00:07:58,559 --> 00:07:59,320
Hurry up and sit over there.

219
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,399
I'll move back a bit.

220
00:08:04,799 --> 00:08:06,079
You sit here.

221
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:06,720
I'll sit a bit further away.

222
00:08:09,679 --> 00:08:10,040
So, well.

223
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:12,239
Today, let's welcome

224
00:08:12,239 --> 00:08:13,399
the two newcomers to the house again.

225
00:08:13,799 --> 00:08:14,079
Cheers.

226
00:08:14,079 --> 00:08:14,839
Thank you.

227
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:15,519
Thank you.

228
00:08:15,519 --> 00:08:16,079
Welcome.

229
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:16,799
Thank you, everyone.

230
00:08:16,799 --> 00:08:17,600
Welcome.

231
00:08:17,959 --> 00:08:18,480
Welcome.

232
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:20,200
How is it?

233
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,440
How does it feel
coming in for the first time?

234
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,040
No particular feeling.

235
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,600
The environment
isn't as good as Hainan's.

236
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,119
But it's a bit cozier than Hainan.

237
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:27,920
The difference between here
and Hainan is

238
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,632
that there isn't a lounger to sleep on.

239
00:08:29,664 --> 00:08:31,808
We can only rest back in our rooms.

240
00:08:31,808 --> 00:08:32,960
That was really comfortable.

241
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,919
But there's a recreation room here.

242
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:34,919
We can watch TV.

243
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:35,679
Yes.

244
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:36,080
We can...

245
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,880
There's also a pet room.

246
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,320
Brother is in there.

247
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,440
The pet room is specially set up for it.

248
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,280
(Brother's exclusive)

249
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,144
That's great.

250
00:08:42,176 --> 00:08:43,880
I think the color scheme here
is quite nice.

251
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:45,159
I felt very familiar
the moment I walked in.

252
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:46,799
I didn't feel any sense
of unfamiliarity.

253
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,119
We're home.

254
00:08:54,479 --> 00:08:55,359
Go back and tidy up.

255
00:08:56,039 --> 00:08:57,760
I'll take my luggage up first.

256
00:08:59,008 --> 00:09:01,536
(Wang Yi's suitcase)

257
00:09:06,336 --> 00:09:08,000
So happy, there's no one across from us.

258
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:10,559
Very happy.

259
00:09:13,248 --> 00:09:13,840
I arranged it.

260
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:20,200
I'm a bit worried about Mr. Dong.

261
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,200
I want to take that...

262
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,159
He's fine.

263
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,159
I checked.

264
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,359
Really fine or just pretending?

265
00:09:24,359 --> 00:09:25,039
Two reasons.

266
00:09:25,039 --> 00:09:25,679
One is that he indeed...

267
00:09:25,679 --> 00:09:26,320
Can't tell?

268
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:27,080
No.

269
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:29,280
First, we ate a lot when we came back,

270
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,080
and he wouldn't really eat much
if he went down anyway.

271
00:09:31,719 --> 00:09:35,080
Second, he wants some quiet time.

272
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,640
He probably wants
to write something down too.

273
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,000
Let's not disturb him.

274
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:39,799
Okay?

275
00:09:40,599 --> 00:09:41,559
Which one is yours?

276
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:43,599
Mine is already pushed
to the stairway entrance.

277
00:09:43,599 --> 00:09:44,080
Okay.

278
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:45,320
But I haven't moved it up yet.

279
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,039
I'll help you with it.

280
00:09:49,719 --> 00:09:50,280
Actually, I think

281
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,719
(Yang Xihui's suitcase)
they deliberately didn't arrange an elevator.

282
00:09:52,919 --> 00:09:53,559
Just to make...

283
00:09:55,119 --> 00:09:55,640
Not bad at all.

284
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:56,919
Welcome home.

285
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,520
I'll get mine.

286
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:58,960
Okay.

287
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:00,960
I'll go with you.

288
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:02,280
Okay.

